The paper deals with computer-generated facial images and their detection by spoofing detectors, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and computer security (cs.CR) sub-categories. The proposed method uses a convolutional neural network (CNN), which is a popular machine learning technique in multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves training the network without gradient information, which is a common approach in adversarial machine learning (cs.AI) sub-category.
